transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, this is Olivia speaking.

Speaker 2: Who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 1: Olivia, this is Brian.

Speaker 2: Is there a Leo there I just talked to?

Speaker 1: Yeah, sure.

Speaker 2: Yeah, do you need to speak to him specifically?

Speaker 1: Well, he just knows what's going on.

Speaker 2: I had canceled my account because I had received a shipment I didn't order,

Speaker 1: and he sent me an okay on everything and all that,

Speaker 2: but he sent the return instructions.

Speaker 1: And I don't drive, and it's hard to get a ride to ship it back to you,

Speaker 2: so I sent an email back to him,

Speaker 1: please just let the charge stand on my card and then go ahead

Speaker 2: and cancel everything after that.

Speaker 1: And I just wanted to explain that to him.

Speaker 2: Go ahead and charge me for this shipment

Speaker 1: so I don't have to try to get to the store and send it back to you.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I can message him that,

Speaker 1: or if you want to talk to him I can send you over to him.

Speaker 2: It's up to you.

Speaker 1: Well, yeah, I don't know if you can take care of it.

Speaker 2: If you can pull up my information.

Speaker 1: Yeah, he did cancel your prescription for you, so that's the good news.

Speaker 2: Yeah, if you're just going to keep those, that's totally fine.

Speaker 1: They didn't work for you, the AGV?

Speaker 2: I don't think it was advertised.

Speaker 1: I guess I was expecting more out of it.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah.

Speaker 1: But I don't care if I keep it and leave that charge.

Speaker 2: I know it's been charged to my credit card already,

Speaker 1: so if that just stays on there before they cancel my account, is that possible?

Speaker 2: Yeah, yeah, he already canceled your prescription,

Speaker 1: and that order you received, it was actually charged like a week ago.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: So just so they know that I'm not returning it.

Speaker 1: I don't know what the procedure is on that.

Speaker 2: I don't want them to keep expecting it,

Speaker 1: and when they don't get it, get mad at me and start emailing me or something on it.

Speaker 2: No, no, that won't happen.

Speaker 1: You don't need to worry about that.

Speaker 2: Okay, well, if you can just put a note in the account that the customer decided to keep it

Speaker 1: rather than having it go through the return process.

Speaker 2: Okay, his most recent order rather than returning.

Speaker 1: Okay, yeah, I just left that.

Speaker 2: You have my information in front of you.

Speaker 1: Your last name is Kraft, K-R-A-F-T.

Speaker 2: Yeah, and you're in Florence, Arizona.

Speaker 1: Correct, you got it.

Speaker 2: March 24th, 48.

Speaker 1: Is that right?

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: So if you could just do that for me, and I'll just stick those in the cabinet,

Speaker 2: and I won't worry about it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah, that's great.

Speaker 2: Okay, well, if you need anything, you know, you always know where to find us,

Speaker 1: but I am sorry that you didn't work out for you.

Speaker 2: Can you just email me a confirmation of our conversation that you put a note in there

Speaker 1: that I'm keeping this thing and whatever, just so I have a record that we talked?

Speaker 2: Oh, sure, sure, yeah.

Speaker 1: Okay, because I sent him two emails and I didn't get an answer back,

Speaker 2: so just so I have something that says I'm keeping it and not returning it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can also let him know separately.

Speaker 2: Okay, appreciate your help.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and thank you, Brian.

Speaker 2: I hope you have a great day.

Speaker 1: All right, you too.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Thanks.

Speaker 2: Bye.
